Swagger & API's
——————————————————————————————————————————
API: Application Programming Interfaces

An API acts as the middleman between an application and web server that want to connect with each other to share information.

Swagger: API documentation that describe the structure of APIs so that machines can read them.
	ie: api paramaters, what it returns, does it need authorization, etc

